line-height:150% !important; } } Dear Griffin Moran, We are excited to see that you have applied for a position at IBM, and we want to ensure that you have the best opportunity to showcase your fantastic skills. We understand that resume alone doesn't always reflect a candidate's full potential. That's why we invite you to complete one or more of the following assessments, which will help us gain a more comprehensive view of your capabilities. IBM values accessibility and are committed to ensuring that every candidate has an equal opportunity to showcase their skills and potential. We support measures like additional time for persons with disabilities on selection assessments. We use following assessments for selection purposes. You will be invited to complete 1 or more of these assessments, depending on the role you are applying for. The next step in the process includes one or more assessments – described below. The Coding Assessment - helps us to understand your level of programming knowledge and ability. You will be presented with a coding interface to solve coding challenges. This is a timed assessment. We believe that these assessments will provide you with a better opportunity to showcase your skills, and we encourage you to take them seriously. We also want to make sure that you feel comfortable and supported throughout the process. All applicants are requested to click the accommodation link below. If you are a person with a disability, please follow the link to submit any adjustments that you require, such as extra time. IBM will review the details of your requirement and work with you on any adjustment options for your application. It is important that you submit your requirements before starting any assessments. If you do not need extra time on the assessments, please mark your response in the link below. Accommodation Form Please note that this form must be completed for each position you apply for that requires an assessment. For additional information and helpful tips, please visit our blog We appreciate your interest in joining our team and wish you the best of luck as you complete these assessments. We can't wait to see all that you have to offer! Sincerely, The IBM Talent Acquisition Team 742850BR Federal Data Engineer Co-Op

Subject: You have successfully submitted your IBM job application.
Body: IBM Careers Thank you for applying Griffin Moran, thank you for applying to the role of Federal Data Engineer Co-Op Ref:742850BR at IBM. We’re excited that you’re considering us as your next employer! Here at IBM, we believe our greatest asset is the IBMer. We strive every day to foster a culture of conscious inclusion for all individuals and provide IBMers the opportunity to make a positive impact on the world while bringing their authentic selves to work. To that end, we want to be as transparent as possible with you about what to expect next now that you’ve applied to IBM. Currently, your application is being reviewed by real IBMers, who are experts in screening resumes in their respective fields. If there's a potential match, we’ll contact you to discuss the next steps of our hiring process. While you wait to hear from us: • Visit our special careers page to find tips on acing your interview and career advice from current IBMers. You can also check out our application process page to learn more about how we hire at IBM. • Connect with us on our Life@IBM social media channels (links in the footer below) where you can engage with us further, discover what life at IBM is like, and see how IBMers around the world are making an impact. You can also check the status of your application at any time by visiting your IBM Career Portal. If you have any questions, please feel free to send us a direct message on any of our social channels. Thank you again, Griffin, for taking the time to apply to IBM and for your interest in becoming a future IBMer. Subject: Thank you for applying to Twilio!
Body: Hi Griffin, Thank you for your interest in a role at Twilio! We just received your application and appreciate your enthusiasm for joining our team. As we approach the holiday season, we want to highlight our commitment to fostering a culture that values both hard work and the importance of taking well-deserved breaks. To support this, Twilio will be observing a company-wide break from December 23rd to January 1st, giving our team the opportunity to disconnect and recharge during this festive time. We understand that job hunting can be stressful, and we aim to be transparent about our hiring process to set you up for success. Here’s what you can expect: Reviewing Your Application Rather than relying on bots and algorithms, Twilio has human recruiters reviewing every application, so it can take a little longer than automated screening. Also, there are no loose ends with us: we'll let you know where you stand either way. Our Interview Process If we like what we see, a recruiting team member will reach out to discuss the opportunity. The next steps could include a few rounds of interviews taking from 2-4 weeks, sometimes longer. While this email doesn't guarantee an interview, we encourage you to check out our Interview Prep Guide ( https://drive.google.com/file/d/15uGbg6AfEbBPt5keqi0NW2ezBPWjaBAD/view ). Even if you don't move forward with us, it's got some great tips for active job seekers. And to get a feel for the Twilio experience, check out our culture page ( https://www.twilio.com/company/culture ) and follow our LinkedIn ( https://www.linkedin.com/company/twilio-inc-/ ). Thanks again for your interest in building the future of communications! Thank you, -Twilio Recruiting Team #WeBuildAtTwilio ( https://www.instagram.com/webuildattwilio/ ) ( https://twitter.com/webuildattwilio?lang=en ) ( https://www.linkedin.com/company/twilio-inc-/ )

A request to release a co-signer requires that the borrower has made consecutive timely payments during the repayment period with no periods of forbearance or deferment. The "repayment period" begins after any In-School and Grace Periods. "Timely payment" means each full principal and interest payment is made no later than the 15th day after the scheduled due date of the payment. "Consecutive payment" means the regularly scheduled monthly payment must be made for 24 months straight for private student loans, and 12 months straight for refinance loans, without any interruption immediately prior to the release request. To qualify for a co-signer release, the borrower must submit a request, meet the consecutive, timely payment requirements, provide proof of income, and pass a credit check.

Subject: Thank you for applying to Airbnb!
Body: Hi Griffin, Thank you for your interest in the Software Engineering Intern role; your application is in good hands! Airbnb Recruiting is closed for the holiday season. We are taking time to reconnect with friends, family, and our community. One of our recruiters will personally review your application upon our return on January 6th, and get back to you within a few weeks. We know how much time and energy go into applying for a job - congratulations on taking this first step! If you have any questions about the hiring process at Airbnb, you might find the answers on our common questions page. Thanks again for your interest and application, we look forward to connecting with you in the New Year. Regards, Airbnb Recruiting Team

We're proud that you're part of the Fitbod family. Happy holidays from our whole team to you and yours. Happy Lifting, Allen and Jesse, Co-founders P.S. Body: Fliffmas Time Is Here! 🎄 ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ------------------------------------------------ Hey Griffm1, ------------------------------------------------ We’re excited to spread the Fliffmas cheer with a variety of holiday offers and rewards for the Fliff Fam starting on Christmas Day! Check out what’s in store 👇🎁 ----------------- Fliffmass Bonus 💵 ----------------- A $49.99 purchase gets you 625,000 Fliff Coins, 5X our standard rates. Head to the Coin Shop in the app to take advantage of this limited time offer. Offer will be available starting on December 25, 2024 and expires on January 5, 2025. ----------------- Gifts for Slips 🎁 ----------------- Get a reward on top of your winning picks. Each day, we’re giving 100 Fliff Cash to 10 lucky winners – that’s 1,000 Fliff Cash everyday! To enter, post any gold or green winning ticket from the prior day’s games on X (formerly known as Twitter) and use the hashtag #fliffmas. Winners will be credited in their Fliff accounts and announced on X at @fliff. Offer will be available starting December 25, 2024 and ends on January 5, 2025. Subject: Big Hair, Big Hopes
Body: ’Tis the season of rekindled Beta bonds, reestablishing chapters and giving back to the Beta experience. View this email [ https://betathetapi.informz.net/InformzDataService/OnlineVersion/Individual?mailingInstanceId=11817885&subscriberId=1170341476 ] in your browser. Beta Theta Pi E-NEWS | DECEMBER 2024 Grant Walther's disappointment was captured during the Georgia-Texas football broadcast. Big Hair, Big Hopes Disappointment set in for Grant Walther, Texas ’27, late in the game as Georgia was on the verge of handing the Longhorns their first loss of the football season back in October. His reaction, captured on the broadcast, quickly went viral, dubbing him "Angry Texas Fan" and "Texas Hair Guy." Now, this Beta brother wants to turn the internet's attention away from him and toward cancer research. Tapping into his internet fame, Brother Walther is 90% of the way to his $20,000 fundraising goal. "When something good happens to you, the best thing to do is just pass it forward," Grant said. Four inducted new members at Hanover with local alumni Historic Iota Chapter Is Back Remember the legend of John Hannah Gray [ https://issuu.com/betathetapiao/docs/01._beta_brotherhood_april_2015/44 ] , Hanover 1856? His historic chapter is back! The Fraternity has worked with a dedicated interest group on campus — led by Iota legacy Joey Theobald ’26, son of Matt Theobald ’96 — since last spring. The first four refounding fathers (pictured above with local alumni) were inducted as new members in early December. Refer a young man to Hanover or another Beta chapter using the button below. Recommend a Man to Beta http://beta.org/recommend graphic with a picture of Beta's marching line with the title "12 Days of Impact" 12 Days of Foundation Impact From scholarships to leadership programming and more, the impact of the Beta experience can be felt across all of North America. In the spirit of the holidays, the Beta Foundation spent the first two weeks of December sharing stories and firsthand accounts on social media of ways the Fraternity has changed young men’s lives with the help of the Beta Leadership Fund. You, too, can expand this impact and create more stories like these with a year-end gift to the BLF. Explore the Impact http://beta.org/12-days five collegiate commissioners from the 2024 cohort pictured at the Beta Campanile during the 186th General Convention Six Selected to Serve as Collegiate Commissioners Collegiate commissioners have proven invaluable in providing a student voice to the Fraternity, Foundation and General Fraternity House Corporation Boards since 2019. Recently appointed by General Secretary John Stebbins, Emory ’92, three brothers — T.J. Hockett, Florida State ’25; Henry Jonas, Appalachian State ’25; and Joseph Kosak, Furman ’26 — join continuing commissioners Christopher Cardenas, Texas ’24; Phillip Miavelstück, George Mason ’25; and Jake Polzin, Minnesota ’24; in their prestigious roles. (Pictured: The 2024 commissioner cohort at the 185th General Convention.) Read More https://www.beta.org/2025-cc/ two photos of christmas decorations at the Oklahoma chapter house Sprucing up the Beta House What's better than a little holiday spirit to further make a chapter house a home? The University of Oklahoma Parent Club brought Christmas cheer to the brothers' home-away-from-home, decorating the Gamma Phi chapter house with a few trees, several wreaths and lots of garland. The deer above the mantel even enjoyed some extra adorning with ornaments in its antlers! As an extra gift, the moms and dads came back this month with "finals week survival bags" for the chapter, offering snacks and well-wishes for members to get them through exams. James Hustace (left) and Ami Bera (right) Election Day Wins Two Beta brothers notched Election Day victories in November. In California, U.S. Representative Ami Bera, UC Irvine ’87, (left) won reelection in his Sacramento-area district. In his seventh term, he will continue on as the longest-serving Indian American in Congress. James Hustace, Lawrence ’08, (right) defeated the incumbent in his race for Hawaii County Council. He's been a long-time community advocate as president of his hometown Waimea Community Association and now earns a district seat to serve the Big Island. Trustee Joel Stern and a group of UC Riverside alumni on the golf course The Alumni's Return More than a dozen UC Riverside brothers gathered for the second annual Epsilon Sigma Chapter Reunion this fall. Though it had been 20 years since many of the men had seen one another, their Beta Spirit was instantly rekindled — even as several battled it out on the fairways in friendly competition. Did you know the Fraternity has 75+ chapter- and geography-based alumni associations? No matter which chapter or city you call home, the opportunity to revisit your Beta roots is within reach! Find an Alumni Association Near You https://my.beta.org/reports/AlumniAssociations/AADirectory.pdf GET TO THE POINT Caught up on the Magazine?: The fall issue of The Beta Theta Pi magazine [ https://issuu.com/betathetapiao/docs/btp-2024-fall ] is hot off the press and in mailboxes across Beta's Broad Domain. Catch up on all of the stories, headlined by a look inside why there is a decreasing trend in young men going to college, and what it means for Beta. Who Receives the Beta Magazine?: Anyone who requests it, including current and former Beta volunteers, Foundation donors, collegiate members and parents. If you no longer receive a copy in the mail but would like to receive a digital copy, update your communication preferences and contact information on MyBeta [ http://my.beta.org ] or call the Administrative Office at 800.800.BETA. Careers and Internships With Beta: The Fraternity is always looking for motivated brothers and Friends of Beta to work (or intern) for the Administrative Office. Current open positions include director of alumni services, chapter development consultant and summer graduate intern; click here to learn more [ http://beta.org/careers ] . Or, learn more about volunteering [ http://beta.org/volunteer ] for the Fraternity! Make Your Year-End Gift: As 2024 comes to a close, the Foundation needs your help to reach the Beta Leadership Fund's year-end goal. Join thousands of brothers and friends by making your tax-deductible gift [ http://gift.beta.org/enewsblf ] before December 31! Share Your Story: The Fraternity's communication team is looking for stories of brothers' successes and achievements to share across Beta's Broad Domain. Submissions through this form [ https://survey.alchemer.com/s3/7782056/Tell-Us-Your-News ] could be considered for Beta's magazine, e-news, social media and other publications. Subject: New Palliative Care Resources from Sentara
Body: Sentara https://view.sentarahealth.com/?qs=26f4aebb2277d209203e492731c9aa45104ed70d99a6dbf8df9186774d618583bcf7fbaf19705a95ff3257efa05d418abd19ea01b0e068cb2d4b2452e0cd00ef View in web browser https://www.sentara.com/ https://www.sentara.com/login https://www.sentara.com/login MyChart http://navigatepalliativecare.com/content/find-palliative-care-now At Sentara, we recognize that managing a serious illness can be challenging. To help, we've added new resources and a new care navigator dedicated to helping you benefit from our palliative care services for serious illnesses in yourself or your loved ones. Our palliative care services act as your GPS, guiding patients through their care journey while addressing symptoms and stress from conditions like cancer, heart disease and more. https://navigatepalliativecare.com/content/find-palliative-care-now PALLIATIVE CARE NEAR YOU Palliative care may be right for you if: - You experience symptoms and stress from a serious illness. - You seek both curative treatment and relief from pain. - You want to actively manage your medical care and improve communication with your healthcare team. - You desire coordinated care for better outcomes and reduced stress for your caregivers. According to the https://www.who.int/news-room/fact-sheets/detail/palliative-care World Health Organization (WHO) , each year, an estimated 56.8 million people are in need of palliative care. Our dedicated palliative care team is here to support you. If you or a loved one could benefit from our services, please reach out for more information. Warm regards, Your Sentara Care Team You're receiving this email because you've opted-in to receive email notifications when we introduce new treatments or service options available to Sentara patients and caregivers. https://www.sentara.com/policies-and-agreements/privacy-policy Privacy Policy https://cloud.sentarahealth.com/sentaracommunicationpreferences?qs=8abf0f9a78a28c4091277cf9815cb74951a40d9d0e26ae2b8f55106e90a2a5751d2144d1278488abee624e6a773324d4 Manage Preferences https://cloud.sentarahealth.com/unsubscribe?qs=8abf0f9a78a28c4091277cf9815cb74951a40d9d0e26ae2b8f55106e90a2a5751d2144d1278488abee624e6a773324d4 Unsubscribe https://www.sentara.com/contact-us Contact Us https://www.facebook.com/sentarahealth https://www.instagram.com/sentarahealth/ https://www.youtube.com/user/SentaraHealthcare/videos https://www.linkedin.com/company/sentara-healthcare/ Sentara Health 1300 Sentara Park, Virginia Beach, VA 23464 (c) 2024 Sentara Health. Subject: 👉 New features, more parity, squashed bugs 🐛
Body: Fitbod put in work this year—check us out! <> <> <> This year, our team put in work like it was trying to PR every day! We launched new features, made massive behind-the-scenes upgrades and inched closer to parity. Of course, there were a few snags—but bugs are made to be squashed—and our team dropped weights on those little suckers left and right. Everything we did this year was to help you live stronger, longer lives. We hope you dig what we've done and stay tuned for even more awesome in 2025. LEARN MORE <> OUR NEWEST FEATURES <> Set Targets Gamified goals, scientifically geared for mega gains. LEARN MORE <> <> Algorithm Updates Made recommendations better and streamlined app flow. LEARN MORE <> <> Health Connect Added third party integration for better workout accuracy. LEARN MORE <> <> Exercise Guide Launched a free guide on our website for all exercises on the app. SEE NOW <> SEE ALL UPDATES <> <> TIPS, MEMES AND ELMO WE HIT 100K ON INSTAGRAM FOLLOW US <> Big things are coming...want to see? NEW: Fitbod's Public Roadmap OPEN NOW <> <> <> <> <> <> Fitbod Store <> Contact us <> Unsubscribe <> To keep getting Fitbod's communications, add team@marketing.fitbod.app to your email contacts.
